Gradient &amp;&amp; Hessian The gradient of a f, d x 1, can be represented as follow $$ 
abla f(x) =  egin{bmatrix}  rac {\partial f(x)} {\partial x_1} 
ewline &hellip;
ewline  rac {\partial f(x)} {\partial x_d} \end{bmatrix} $$ and the Hessian, d x d, can be represented as $$ 
abla^2 f(x) =  egin{bmatrix}  rac {\partial^2 f(x)} {\partial x_1^2} &amp;  rac {\partial^2 f(x)} {\partial x_1x_2} &amp;  rac {\partial^2 f(x)} {\partial x_1x_d} 
ewline &hellip; &amp; &hellip; &amp; &hellip;
ewline  rac {\partial^2 f(x)} {\partial x_d^2} &amp;  rac {\partial^2 f(x)} {\partial x_dx_2} &amp;  rac {\partial^2 f(x)} {\partial x_dx_d} 
ewline \end{bmatrix} $$
